this has been a good day for me..to read all the info on ptsd as seen by a child of a  parent that was a vet.<br><br>
i always wonderd why my father wouln't talk about wwll. he was a B-25 pilot in north africa, flew a lota missions, and told me once the reason he wouldn't go to church with my mom and us kids was he didn't like god very much, his reason was simple. my dad was straffing and killing a lota people and he didn't think god was very fair in the way helpless ppl got in the way and were killed also.<br><br>
didn't enter my mind until today what a trauma he'd been thru...flying formation in flak you could walk on...bombing runs etc...<br><br>
he won't talk about it to this day and he's 77 now...
